        "text": "Heil. Sage",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", I. p. 243, de Wette, Ritschl, Holtzmann, Eichthal). This judgment applies an inappropriate standard to the special relation in which Jesus stood to the Pharisees, seeing that when confronting them He felt a higher destiny than the maintenance of the respect due to a host moving Him (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
